.TH KITTEN 1 "July 2026" "kitten 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kitten \- print source trees with metadata and inline text previews
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kitten
.RI [ OPTION ]...\&
.RI [ PATH ]...\&
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kitten
prints a sorted tree for each requested path. Regular files include their size
and, by default, a bounded text preview. Directories, symbolic links, and
special files are identified explicitly.
.PP
With no path operand, the current directory is inspected. When exactly one
operand names a real directory, kitten changes to that directory and prints it
as
.BR ./ .
With multiple operands, each operand is printed as a separate root.
.PP
Symbolic links are never followed. Binary and oversized files are identified
without printing their contents. Options may appear before or after operands;
.B \-\-
ends option parsing.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Content preview
.TP
.BR \-m " " BYTES ", " \-\-max\-bytes= BYTES
Set the maximum size of a file eligible for preview. The default is 256K.
The suffix K, M, or G multiplies the value by 1024, 1048576, or 1073741824.
The long option also accepts a separated value.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-content
Print only the tree and file metadata.
.TP
.BR \-\-content= auto | never
Select the preview mode. The value
.B auto
enables normal text previews;
.B never
disables them. A separated value is also accepted.
.TP
.B \-\-raw\-content
Print file contents without escaping control bytes. Names and symbolic-link
targets remain escaped. This option should be used only with trusted files.
.SS Traversal and filtering
.TP
.BR \-L " " DEPTH ", " \-\-depth= DEPTH
Descend at most DEPTH levels. Zero prints only the root, and one includes the
root's immediate children. A negative value is invalid.
.TP
.BR \-\-exclude= PATTERN
Skip names or paths matched by the shell-style PATTERN. Matching is performed
against the entry name, its displayed relative path, and the same path without
a leading
.BR ./ .
This option may be repeated and also accepts a separated value.
.TP
.B \-\-dirs\-only
Print and descend into real directories only. Regular files, symbolic links,
and special entries are skipped.
.TP
.BR \-U ", " \-\-unsorted
Use filesystem order instead of sorting. This mode retains only one pending
entry and keeps memory bounded for very large directories.
.SS Output format
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-human\-readable
Print sizes in IEC binary units such as KiB and MiB. Exact byte counts are the
default.
.TP
.B \-\-ascii
Force portable ASCII tree branches. Without this option, Unicode is selected
for a UTF-8 locale and ASCII is used otherwise.
.TP
.B \-\-unicode
Force Unicode tree branches regardless of the locale. If both branch-style
options are present, the last one wins.
.TP
.B \-\-summary
Print directory, file, symbolic-link, special-file, byte, skipped, and error
totals after traversal.
.TP
.BR \-\-language= auto | en | ru
Select the message language. The default,
.BR auto ,
uses Russian for a Russian message locale and English otherwise. Option names
and values remain English. A separated value is also accepted.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the program version and license summary, then exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a detailed option summary and exit.
.SH PATH OPERANDS
A path consisting of a single hyphen is treated as a literal path. Any other
path beginning with a hyphen must follow
.BR \-\- .
Entries inside directories are sorted according to the active locale unless
.B \-\-unsorted
is active.
.PP
Exclude patterns use
.BR fnmatch (3)
semantics. A slash in a pattern separates path components; wildcards do not
cross that slash.
.SH PREVIEWS
Only regular files are previewed. After a non-blocking, no-follow open, the
descriptor size is compared with the configured limit. A file with a NUL byte
anywhere in that range is reported as binary. A file that grows beyond the
limit while being inspected is reported as skipped.
.PP
The default preview mode preserves line boundaries and tabs. It escapes other
ASCII control bytes, multibyte control characters, DEL, and invalid encoded
bytes. With
.BR \-\-raw\-content ,
file data is printed without that escaping.
Empty, unreadable, binary, oversized, and changing files receive explicit labels.
.SH LOCALIZATION
The program initializes the process locale and translates help, diagnostics,
metadata labels, preview status messages, and summaries into English or
Russian. Paths and file contents are not translated.
.PP
Use
.B \-\-language
when output must not depend on the environment. System error strings are
provided by the platform C library and may follow a locale unsupported by
kitten itself.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LC_ALL
Overrides all locale categories when set.
.TP
.B LC_MESSAGES
Selects the message locale when LC_ALL is unset.
.TP
.B LANG
Supplies the fallback locale.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All requested paths were inspected successfully, or help/version output was
requested.
.TP
.B 1
An argument was invalid, a requested operation failed, memory was exhausted,
or an output stream reported an error.
.PP
Skipping binary or oversized previews is not an error.
.SH PORTABILITY
kitten requires C99 and POSIX.1-2008. It is intended for GNU/Linux and BSD
systems. Native non-POSIX directory traversal, including the Windows API, is
outside its supported scope.
.SH SECURITY
Names and symbolic-link targets are always escaped so embedded newlines and
terminal control bytes cannot alter the tree display. File preview escaping is
enabled by default. Raw content may contain terminal control sequences, so
.B \-\-raw\-content
should only be used for trusted input.
.PP
kitten does not follow symbolic links, but it is not a transactional snapshot.
Opened files and directories must retain the device and inode reported by the
preceding status check. Results may still reflect concurrent changes to file
contents or ancestor path components during a traversal.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
kitten
kitten --no-content --summary src
kitten -L 2 -m 64K --exclude=.git .
kitten --language=ru --human-readable README.md
kitten --unsorted --no-content /very/large/directory
kitten -- --path-starting-with-a-dash
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/kitten
Default installed executable location.
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/man/man1/kitten.1
Default installed manual location.
